Project Overview

Build a Personal Banking API that manages customer accounts, transactions, and provides financial insights.
This project will challenge you to apply everything you've learned while introducing real-world banking scenarios.


Learning Objectives
This project will help you practice:

✅ All CRUD operations (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
✅ Complex Pydantic models with validation
✅ Computed fields for financial calculations
✅ Query parameters for filtering and searching
✅ Path parameters for specific resource access
✅ Error handling with appropriate status codes
✅ Data transformations between JSON, Pydantic, and dictionaries
✅ Business logic implementation (interest calculation, balance updates)
✅ Request body validation

New Challenges:

🆕 Handling relationships between data (accounts and transactions)
🆕 Implementing business rules (can't withdraw more than balance)
🆕 Date/time handling for transactions
🆕 Aggregation and calculations (total balance, monthly spending)


1- Part 1 --> Create two JSON files: accounts.json - Customer bank accounts, transactions.json - Transaction history

